data.title: About: Band-e Amir, Fars
data.meta_description: Band-e Amir (Persian: بندامير, also Romanized as Band-e Amīr and Bandāmir) is a village in Band-e Amir Rural District, Zarqan District, Shiraz County, Fars Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 1,424, in 370 families.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

Band-e Amir (Persian: بندامير, also Romanized as Band-e Amīr and Bandāmir) is a village in Band-e Amir Rural District, Zarqan District, Shiraz County, Fars Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 1,424, in 370 families. (en)
